wfFddiEntry.name: wfFddiEntry
wfFddiEntry.description: An entry in the FDDI table

wfFDDIState.name: wfFDDIState
wfFDDIState.description: Line driver state variable, not present, init, down, up.

wfFDDISlot.name: wfFDDISlot
wfFDDISlot.description: Instance ID slot - filled in by driver.

wfFDDINode.name: wfFDDINode
wfFDDINode.description: Instance ID node - filled in by driver. For the ASN this attribute is an encoded value and is equal to 'module'*10 + 'node'. Where 'module' is defined in attribute 50 and 'node' is defined in attribute 51 of this table. For non-ASN platforms this attribute indicates the physical node number on the slot

wfFDDICct.name: wfFDDICct
wfFDDICct.description: Cct number for this line instance.

wfFDDIBofl.name: wfFDDIBofl
wfFDDIBofl.description: The Breath-Of-Life (BOFL) function, when enabled, will disable the LLC interface when the FDDI becomes non-operational (i.e., link unavailable) and the following conditions are true: 1. The wfFddiMacMaUnitDataEnable attribute is enabled. 2. The BOFL timer expired (specified by wfFDDIBoflTmo). If this attribute is disabled, the LLC interface will be terminated immediately after the link becomes unavailable.

wfFDDIBoflTmo.name: wfFDDIBoflTmo
wfFDDIBoflTmo.description: Specifies the time value (in seconds) of the BOFL timer. The BOFL timer will be set to the value of this attribute when the following conditions are true: 1. The wfFDDIBofl attribute is enabled. 2. The link becomes unavailable. Upon expiration of the BOFL timer, the LLC interface will be disabled. Note also that the BOFL timer will be disabled if the link becomes operational (available) before the timer expires..

wfFDDIMtu.name: wfFDDIMtu
wfFDDIMtu.description: The MTU is the maximum allowed frame length on the wire, excluding frame delimiters (i.e. preamble, ending delimiter). The MTU of an FDDI frame includes: FC (1 octet) + DA (6 octets) + SA (6 octets) + INFO (<= 4478 octets) + FCS (4 octets) = 4495 octets

wfFDDIMadr.name: wfFDDIMadr
wfFDDIMadr.description: PROM-based MAC address, fixed - line driver fills in.

wfFDDIOctetsRxOk.name: wfFDDIOctetsRxOk
wfFDDIOctetsRxOk.description: Number of bytes received without error. This byte count only includes LLC frames (i.e. no MAC and SMT frames).

wfFDDIFramesRxOk.name: wfFDDIFramesRxOk
wfFDDIFramesRxOk.description: Number of frames received without error. This frame count only includes LLC frames (i.e. no MAC and SMT frames).

wfFDDIOctetsTxOk.name: wfFDDIOctetsTxOk
wfFDDIOctetsTxOk.description: Number of bytes transmitted without error. This byte count only includes LLC and SMT frames (i.e. no MAC frames).

wfFDDIFramesTxOk.name: wfFDDIFramesTxOk
wfFDDIFramesTxOk.description: Number of frames transmitted without error. This frame count only includes LLC and SMT frames (i.e. no MAC frames ).

wfFDDICrcErrRx.name: wfFDDICrcErrRx
wfFDDICrcErrRx.description: Number of frames received with CRC errors.

wfFDDIOverrunRx.name: wfFDDIOverrunRx
wfFDDIOverrunRx.description: Number of frames received with internal overrun errors.

wfFDDIParityErrRx.name: wfFDDIParityErrRx
wfFDDIParityErrRx.description: Number of frames received with parity errors.

wfFDDIMacErrRx.name: wfFDDIMacErrRx
wfFDDIMacErrRx.description: Number of frames received with MAC errors.

wfFDDIRingErrRx.name: wfFDDIRingErrRx
wfFDDIRingErrRx.description: Number of receive ring error events.

wfFDDISmtRingErrRx.name: wfFDDISmtRingErrRx
wfFDDISmtRingErrRx.description: Number of SMT receive ring error events.

wfFDDIRingOverrunRx.name: wfFDDIRingOverrunRx
wfFDDIRingOverrunRx.description: Number of LLC receive ring overrun events.

wfFDDISmtRingOverrunRx.name: wfFDDISmtRingOverrunRx
wfFDDISmtRingOverrunRx.description: Number of SMT receive ring overrun events.

wfFDDIAbortTx.name: wfFDDIAbortTx
wfFDDIAbortTx.description: Number of transmit frames with internal abort errors.

wfFDDIUnderrunTx.name: wfFDDIUnderrunTx
wfFDDIUnderrunTx.description: Number of transmit frames aborted with underrun errors.

wfFDDIParityErrTx.name: wfFDDIParityErrTx
wfFDDIParityErrTx.description: Number of transmit frames aborted with parity errors.

wfFDDIRingErrTx.name: wfFDDIRingErrTx
wfFDDIRingErrTx.description: Number of LLC/SMT transmit ring error events.

wfFDDIPortOpErr.name: wfFDDIPortOpErr
wfFDDIPortOpErr.description: Number of port operation error events.

wfFDDIInternOpErr.name: wfFDDIInternOpErr
wfFDDIInternOpErr.description: Number of internal operation error events.

wfFDDISmtConnectionPolicy.name: wfFDDISmtConnectionPolicy
wfFDDISmtConnectionPolicy.description: A value that indicates the connection policies enforced at the station. A station sets the corresponding policy for each of the connection types that it rejects. The letter designations, X and Y, in the 'rejectX-Y' names have the following significance: X represents the PC-Type of the local PORT and Y represents a PC-Neighbor in the evaluation of Connection-Policy (PC-Type, PC- Neighbor) that is done to determine the setting of T-Val(3) in the PC-Signaling sequence. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each of the connection policies currently enforced on the node, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Policy Power rejectA-A 0 rejectA-B 1 rejectA-S 2 rejectA-M 3 rejectB-A 4 rejectB-B 5 rejectB-S 6 rejectB-M 7 rejectS-A 8 rejectS-B 9 rejectS-S 10 rejectS-M 11 rejectM-A 12 rejectM-B 13 rejectM-S 14 rejectM-M 15

wfFDDISmtTNotify.name: wfFDDISmtTNotify
wfFDDISmtTNotify.description: The timer used in the Neighbor Notification protocol, reported in seconds and ranging from 2 to 30 seconds.

wfFDDIMacTReq.name: wfFDDIMacTReq
wfFDDIMacTReq.description: Specifies the maximum time value of 'wfFddiPathMaxTReq' that shall be used by any MAC that is configured in this path. The operational value of 'wfFddiPathMaxTReq' is managed by setting this attribute. This attribute has the time value range of: wfFddiPathTvxLowerBound < wfFddiMacTReq <= wfFddiPathTMaxLowerBound. Time specified in octet units. The default value of this attribute is 165 msec. The name of this attribute in the IETF MIB is FddiMibPATHMaxTReq. To convert 165 milliseconds to octet units of 80 nanaseconds: T_Req Nanaoseconds = ((165 * 1000 * 1000) / 80) = 2062500 To convert 2062500 octet units of 80 nanoseconds to milliseconds: T_Req Milliseconds = ((2062500 / 12.5) / 1000) = 165

wfFDDIMacTMax.name: wfFDDIMacTMax
wfFDDIMacTMax.description: The requested maximum TTRT to be supported by a MAC represented in unsigned integer specifying time in octet units (80 nanoseconds).

wfFDDIMacTvxValue.name: wfFDDIMacTvxValue
wfFDDIMacTvxValue.description: The requested value of TvxValue represented in unsigned integer specifying time in octet units (80 nanoseconds).

wfFDDIMacTMin.name: wfFDDIMacTMin
wfFDDIMacTMin.description: The requested minimum TTRT to be requested by a MAC represented in unsigned integer specifying time in octet units (80 nanoseconds).

wfFDDISmtEnable.name: wfFDDISmtEnable
wfFDDISmtEnable.description: Enable Station Management periodic timer and NIF protocol.

wfFDDITxClipFrames.name: wfFDDITxClipFrames
wfFDDITxClipFrames.description: Number of frames clipped in driver's transmit routine due to transmit congestion.

wfFDDIRxReplenMisses.name: wfFDDIRxReplenMisses
wfFDDIRxReplenMisses.description: Number of packet buffer misses while attempting to replenish driver receive ring.

wfFDDICfgTxQueueLength.name: wfFDDICfgTxQueueLength
wfFDDICfgTxQueueLength.description: Configured Transmit Queue Length. Values other than zero over-ride the router selected values. A value of zero has a special meaning. Zero causes router based default values to be used. Values larger than the compiled ring size are truncated to the compiled ring size.

wfFDDICfgRxQueueLength.name: wfFDDICfgRxQueueLength
wfFDDICfgRxQueueLength.description: Configured Receive Queue Length. Values other than zero over-ride the router selected values. A value of zero has a special meaning. Zero cuases router based default values to be used. Values larger than the compiled ring size are truncated to the compiled ring size.

wfFDDILineNumber.name: wfFDDILineNumber
wfFDDILineNumber.description: Logical line number associated with this driver entity.

wfFDDIForcePeerTree.name: wfFDDIForcePeerTree
wfFDDIForcePeerTree.description: This attribute allows all FDDI Peer/Tree connections to reach the 'Thru' state. This is done to give the user some flexibility and allow them to Daisy Chain their Phy connections, mixing Tree & Peer connections. This type of daisy chaining DOES NOT conform to the SMT standard and is NOT recommended as it may result in a less than optimum token path. Normally when we have a Peer/Tree connection mix, we will wrap the connection, favoring PHY B.

wfFDDIInvalidFrameStatusRx.name: wfFDDIInvalidFrameStatusRx
wfFDDIInvalidFrameStatusRx.description: A count of the number of badly formed frames received off of the FDDI ring. These are frames which do not contain a valid Frame Status field of at least 3 control indicator symbols (i.e. E, A, C, flags).

wfFDDIRxOversizedFrames.name: wfFDDIRxOversizedFrames
wfFDDIRxOversizedFrames.description: Number of LLC frames received whose length exceeded the MTU.

wfFDDIRxSmtOversizedFrames.name: wfFDDIRxSmtOversizedFrames
wfFDDIRxSmtOversizedFrames.description: Number of SMT frames received whose length exceeded the MTU.

wfFDDIRxUndersizedFrames.name: wfFDDIRxUndersizedFrames
wfFDDIRxUndersizedFrames.description: Number of LLC frames received whose length was less than 20 bytes including the FC byte and a 4 byte CRC.

wfFDDIRxSmtUndersizedFrames.name: wfFDDIRxSmtUndersizedFrames
wfFDDIRxSmtUndersizedFrames.description: Number of SMT frames received whose length was less than 37 bytes including the FC byte and a 4 byte CRC.

wfFDDIModule.name: wfFDDIModule
wfFDDIModule.description: Module number for ASN platform, filled in by driver. For non-ASN platforms this attribute will not be used.

wfFDDIActualNode.name: wfFDDIActualNode
wfFDDIActualNode.description: Actual Node number for ASN platform, filled in by driver. For non-ASN platforms, this attribute will not be used.

wfFDDILastChange.name: wfFDDILastChange
wfFDDILastChange.description: The value of SysUpTime at the time the interface entered it's current operational state (UP state). SysUpTime is defined as the time (in hundredths of a second) since the network management portion of the system was last re-initialized. Usually the time since boot.

wfFDDIOutQLen.name: wfFDDIOutQLen
wfFDDIOutQLen.description: The instantaneous current length of the output packet queue (in packets).

wfFDDIRxSmtOctets.name: wfFDDIRxSmtOctets
wfFDDIRxSmtOctets.description: Number of bytes received without error. This byte count only includes SMT frames (i.e. no MAC and LLC frames).

wfFDDIRxSmtFrames.name: wfFDDIRxSmtFrames
wfFDDIRxSmtFrames.description: Number of frames received without error. This frame count only includes SMT frames (i.e. no MAC and LLC frames).

wfFDDIIntProcessings.name: wfFDDIIntProcessings
wfFDDIIntProcessings.description: Counts the number of times the interrupt service routine has been called

wfFDDITxProcessings.name: wfFDDITxProcessings
wfFDDITxProcessings.description: Counts the number of times the transmit routine fsi_xmt_oper_act(), has been called

wfFDDIRxProcessings.name: wfFDDIRxProcessings
wfFDDIRxProcessings.description: Counts the number of times RINT processing takes place in the interrupt service routine.

wfFDDITxRNRProcessings.name: wfFDDITxRNRProcessings
wfFDDITxRNRProcessings.description: Counts the number of times the transmit complete routine fsi_xmt_cmpl(), has been called

wfFDDISmtRxProcessings.name: wfFDDISmtRxProcessings
wfFDDISmtRxProcessings.description: Counts the number of time RINT was processing was performed on the SMT receive ring.

wfFDDIPhyALogPtr.name: wfFDDIPhyALogPtr
wfFDDIPhyALogPtr.description: Address of the Debug Phy Event Buffer for Phy A. This attribute is strictly for diagnostic purposes. The size of the buffer is 1028 bytes.

wfFDDIPhyBLogPtr.name: wfFDDIPhyBLogPtr
wfFDDIPhyBLogPtr.description: Address of the Debug Phy Event Buffer for Phy B. This attribute is strictly for diagnostic purposes. The size of the buffer is 1028 bytes.

wfFDDIPromiscuous.name: wfFDDIPromiscuous
wfFDDIPromiscuous.description: For now this attribute is used only in BNX code !!! The promiscuous parameter allows address filtering based on the destination MAC addresses. When enabled, all frames are received, disabled indicates only frames destined for this local address and any functional group address are received.

wfFDDILLCFrameControl.name: wfFDDILLCFrameControl
wfFDDILLCFrameControl.description: Frame control used for LLC frames, using synchronous frames for reserved priority traffic when specified.

wfFDDITurboBofl.name: wfFDDITurboBofl
wfFDDITurboBofl.description: DEBUG parameter - Turbo bofl enabled or disabled, by adjusting BoflNum and BoflLen bofl packets can be made to fill the links available bandwith. This function is not a faster parallel of the wfFDDIBofl feature it does not opperate on a disabled LLC interface

wfFDDIBoflNum.name: wfFDDIBoflNum
wfFDDIBoflNum.description: DEBUG parameter - Number of breath of life packets per breath of life

wfFDDIBoflLen.name: wfFDDIBoflLen
wfFDDIBoflLen.description: DEBUG parameter - breath of life packet length

wfFddiSmtEntry.name: wfFddiSmtEntry
wfFddiSmtEntry.description: A SMT entry containing information common to a given SMT.

wfFddiSmtSlot.name: wfFddiSmtSlot
wfFddiSmtSlot.description: Slot number associated with an SMT entity.

wfFddiSmtNode.name: wfFddiSmtNode
wfFddiSmtNode.description: Node/connector number associated with an SMT entity.

wfFddiSmtCct.name: wfFddiSmtCct
wfFddiSmtCct.description: Circuit number associated with an SMT entity.

wfFddiSmtStationId.name: wfFddiSmtStationId
wfFddiSmtStationId.description: Unique identifier of an FDDI station.

wfFddiSmtOpVersionId.name: wfFddiSmtOpVersionId
wfFddiSmtOpVersionId.description: The version that this station is using for its operation.

wfFddiSmtMacCt.name: wfFddiSmtMacCt
wfFddiSmtMacCt.description: The number of MACs in a station.

wfFddiSmtNonMasterCt.name: wfFddiSmtNonMasterCt
wfFddiSmtNonMasterCt.description: The number of non master ports (A, B, or S PORTs) in a station.

wfFddiSmtEcmState.name: wfFddiSmtEcmState
wfFddiSmtEcmState.description: Indicates the current state of the ECM state machine.

wfFddiSmtCfState.name: wfFddiSmtCfState
wfFddiSmtCfState.description: The attachment configuration for a station.

wfFddiSmtBypassPresent.name: wfFddiSmtBypassPresent
wfFddiSmtBypassPresent.description: A flag indicating if the station has an optical bypass on its A/B port pair.

wfFddiSmtRemoteDisconnectFlag.name: wfFddiSmtRemoteDisconnectFlag
wfFddiSmtRemoteDisconnectFlag.description: A flag indicating that the station was remotely disconnected from the network as a result of receiving an 'wfFddiSmtStationAction' disconnect in a Parameter Management Frame. A station requires a Connect Action to rejoin & clear the flag.

wfFddiSmtStationStatus.name: wfFddiSmtStationStatus
wfFddiSmtStationStatus.description: This variable indicates the current state of the primary and secondary paths within this station.

wfFddiSmtPeerWrapFlag.name: wfFddiSmtPeerWrapFlag
wfFddiSmtPeerWrapFlag.description: This variable assumes the value of the 'PeerWrapFlag' in CFM.

wfFddiSmtExtTable.name: wfFddiSmtExtTable
wfFddiSmtExtTable.description: A list of SMT extension entries.

wfFddiSmtExtEntry.name: wfFddiSmtExtEntry
wfFddiSmtExtEntry.description: A SMT entry containing information common to a given SMT.

wfFddiSmtExtSlot.name: wfFddiSmtExtSlot
wfFddiSmtExtSlot.description: Slot number associated with an SMT entity.

wfFddiSmtExtNode.name: wfFddiSmtExtNode
wfFddiSmtExtNode.description: Node/connector number associated with an SMT entity.

wfFddiSmtExtCct.name: wfFddiSmtExtCct
wfFddiSmtExtCct.description: Circuit number associated with an SMT entity.

wfFddiSmtHiVersionId.name: wfFddiSmtHiVersionId
wfFddiSmtHiVersionId.description: The highest version of SMT that this station supports.

wfFddiSmtLoVersionId.name: wfFddiSmtLoVersionId
wfFddiSmtLoVersionId.description: The lowest version of SMT that this station supports.

wfFddiSmtManufacturerData.name: wfFddiSmtManufacturerData
wfFddiSmtManufacturerData.description: Contains 32 Octets of manufacturer data. The first component, manufacturing OUI, is the 3 octet Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI) assigned by IEEE. The second component, ManufacturerData, is the manufacturers data (29 octets).

wfFddiSmtUserData.name: wfFddiSmtUserData
wfFddiSmtUserData.description: Contains 32 Octets of user defined information in ascii format.

wfFddiSmtMibVersionId.name: wfFddiSmtMibVersionId
wfFddiSmtMibVersionId.description: The version of the FDDI MIB of this station.

wfFddiSmtMasterCts.name: wfFddiSmtMasterCts
wfFddiSmtMasterCts.description: The number of M ports in a node.

wfFddiSmtAvailablePaths.name: wfFddiSmtAvailablePaths
wfFddiSmtAvailablePaths.description: A bit string that indicates the path types that are available in the station. The value initially takes the value 0, then for each type of path that this node has available, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Path Power ---- ----- Primary 0 Secondary 1 Local 2 For example, a station having Primary and Local paths available would have a value of 5 (2**0 + 2**2).

wfFddiSmtConfigCapabilities.name: wfFddiSmtConfigCapabilities
wfFddiSmtConfigCapabilities.description: A bit string which indicates the configuration capabilities of a node. The 'Hold Available' bit indicates the support of the optional Hold function, which is controlled by 'wfFddiSmtConfigPolicy'. The 'CF-Wrap-AB' bit indicates that the station has the capability of performing a wrab_ab. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value 0, then for each of the configuration policies currently enforced on the node, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Policy Power ------ ----- HoldAvailable 0 CF_Wrap-AB 1

wfFddiSmtConfigPolicy.name: wfFddiSmtConfigPolicy
wfFddiSmtConfigPolicy.description: A bit string representing the configuration policies currently desired in a node. 'Hold' is one of the terms used for the 'Hold' flag.

wfFddiSmtStatRptPolicy.name: wfFddiSmtStatRptPolicy
wfFddiSmtStatRptPolicy.description: If ENABLED, indicates that the node will generate Status Report Frames (SRF) for its implemented events.

wfFddiSmtTraceMaxExpiration.name: wfFddiSmtTraceMaxExpiration
wfFddiSmtTraceMaxExpiration.description: Maximum propogation time for a Trace on an FDDI topology. The value is stored in milliseconds.

wfFddiSmtTimeStamp.name: wfFddiSmtTimeStamp
wfFddiSmtTimeStamp.description: Holds the time of creation of the last Status Report Frame (SRF).

wfFddiSmtTransitionTimeStamp.name: wfFddiSmtTransitionTimeStamp
wfFddiSmtTransitionTimeStamp.description: Holds the time of occurrence of the last condition or event.

wfFddiSmtDatProtocol.name: wfFddiSmtDatProtocol
wfFddiSmtDatProtocol.description: SMT will implement an optional ANSI duplicate address test involving periodic transmission of NSA NIF frames addressed to itself if enabled by this attribute.

wfFddiSmtActionTable.name: wfFddiSmtActionTable
wfFddiSmtActionTable.description: A list of SMT action entries.

wfFddiSmtActionEntry.name: wfFddiSmtActionEntry
wfFddiSmtActionEntry.description: An SMT entry containing actions common to a given SMT.

wfFddiSmtActionSlot.name: wfFddiSmtActionSlot
wfFddiSmtActionSlot.description: Slot number associated with an SMT action entity.

wfFddiSmtActionNode.name: wfFddiSmtActionNode
wfFddiSmtActionNode.description: Node/connector number associated with an SMT action entity.

wfFddiSmtActionCct.name: wfFddiSmtActionCct
wfFddiSmtActionCct.description: Circuit number associated with an SMT action entity.

wfFddiSmtStationAction.name: wfFddiSmtStationAction
wfFddiSmtStationAction.description: This object when read, always returns a value of other(1). The behavior of setting this variable to each of the acceptable values is as follows: Other: Results in a BadValue error Connect: Generates a connect signal to ECM to begin a connection sequence. The 'wfFddiSmtRemoteDisconnectFlag' is cleared on the setting of this variable to 1. Disconnect: Generates a disconnect signal to ECM and sets the 'wfFddiSmtRemoteDisconnectFlag' to TRUE. Path_Test: Initiates a station path test. The 'PathTest' variable is set to 'Testing'. The results of this action are not specified in the standard. Self_test: Initiates a station self test. The results of this action are not specified in the standard. Disable_A: Disable_A causes a PC_Disable on the A port if the A port mode is peer. Disable_B: Disable_B causes a PC_Disable on the B port if the B port mode is peer. Disable_M: Disable_M causes a PC_Disable on all M ports. Attempts to set this object to all other values results in a BadValue error. Agents may elect to return a BadValue error on attempts to set this variable to PathTest or SelfTest.

wfFddiMacEntry.name: wfFddiMacEntry
wfFddiMacEntry.description: A MAC entry containing information common to a given MAC.

wfFddiMacSlot.name: wfFddiMacSlot
wfFddiMacSlot.description: Slot number associated with a MAC entity.

wfFddiMacNode.name: wfFddiMacNode
wfFddiMacNode.description: Node/connector number associated with a MAC entity.

wfFddiMacCct.name: wfFddiMacCct
wfFddiMacCct.description: Circuit number associated with a MAC entity.

wfFddiMacUpstreamNbr.name: wfFddiMacUpstreamNbr
wfFddiMacUpstreamNbr.description: The MAC's upstream neighbor's long individual MAC address. It may be determined by the Neighbor Information Frame protocol. The value shall be reported as '00 00 00 00 00 00' if it is unknown. SMT uses the MSB form for representation of 48-bit addresses.

wfFddiMacDownstreamNbr.name: wfFddiMacDownstreamNbr
wfFddiMacDownstreamNbr.description: The MAC's downstream neighbor's long individual MAC address. It may be determined by the Neighbor Information Frame protocol. The value shall be reported as '00 00 00 00 00 00' if it is unknown. SMT uses the MSB form for representation of 48-bit addresses.

wfFddiMacSmtAddress.name: wfFddiMacSmtAddress
wfFddiMacSmtAddress.description: The 48 bit individual address of the MAC used for SMT frames. SMT uses the MSB form for representation of 48-bit addresses.

wfFddiMacTNeg.name: wfFddiMacTNeg
wfFddiMacTNeg.description: The negotiated TTRT during the claim process represented as an unsigned integer specifying time in nanoseconds.

wfFddiMacRmtState.name: wfFddiMacRmtState
wfFddiMacRmtState.description: Indicates the current state of the Ring Management state machine.

wfFddiMacOldUpstreamNbr.name: wfFddiMacOldUpstreamNbr
wfFddiMacOldUpstreamNbr.description: The previous value of the MAC's upstream neighbor's long individual MAC address. It has an initial value of the SMT-Unknown-MAC Address and is only modified as specified by the Neighbor Information Frame protocol. SMT uses the MSB form for representation of 48-bit addresses.

wfFddiMacOldDownstreamNbr.name: wfFddiMacOldDownstreamNbr
wfFddiMacOldDownstreamNbr.description: The previous value of the MAC's downstream neighbor's long individual MAC address. It has an initial value of the SMT-Unknown-MAC Address and is only modified as specified by the Neighbor Information Frame protocol. SMT uses the MSB form for representation of 48-bit addresses.

wfFddiMacTokenCts.name: wfFddiMacTokenCts
wfFddiMacTokenCts.description: A count that should as closely as possible match the number of times the station has received a token (total of non-restricted and restricted) on this MAC. This count is valuable for determination of network load.

wfFddiMacErrorCts.name: wfFddiMacErrorCts
wfFddiMacErrorCts.description: A count of the number of frames that were detected in error by this MAC that had not been detected in error by another MAC.

wfFddiMacLostCts.name: wfFddiMacLostCts
wfFddiMacLostCts.description: A count of the number of instances that this MAC detected a format error during frame reception such that the frame was stripped.

wfFddiMacDaFlag.name: wfFddiMacDaFlag
wfFddiMacDaFlag.description: Duplicate Address Flag. An RMT flag used to indicate that the MAC under control has the same address as another MAC on the FDDI.

wfFddiMacUnaDaFlag.name: wfFddiMacUnaDaFlag
wfFddiMacUnaDaFlag.description: A flag, UNDA_Flag, set when the upstream neighbor reports a duplicate address condition. Cleared once the condition clears.

wfFddiMacFrameErrorFlag.name: wfFddiMacFrameErrorFlag
wfFddiMacFrameErrorFlag.description: Indicates the MAC Frame Error Condition is present when set. Cleared when the condition clears and on station initialization.

wfFddiMacMaUnitDataAvailable.name: wfFddiMacMaUnitDataAvailable
wfFddiMacMaUnitDataAvailable.description: A flag indicating that the MAC is available for the transmission and reception of Protocol Data Units (PDUs). The MAC and LLC interface will be established when the wfFddiMacMaUnitDataEnable attribute is enabled.

wfFddiMacDownstreamPortType.name: wfFddiMacDownstreamPortType
wfFddiMacDownstreamPortType.description: Indicates the PC-Type of the first port that is downstream of this MAC (the exit port).

wfFddiMacExtTable.name: wfFddiMacExtTable
wfFddiMacExtTable.description: A list of MAC extension entries.

wfFddiMacExtEntry.name: wfFddiMacExtEntry
wfFddiMacExtEntry.description: A MAC entry containing information common to a given MAC.

wfFddiMacExtSlot.name: wfFddiMacExtSlot
wfFddiMacExtSlot.description: Slot number associated with a MAC entity.

wfFddiMacExtNode.name: wfFddiMacExtNode
wfFddiMacExtNode.description: Node/connector number associated with a MAC entity.

wfFddiMacExtCct.name: wfFddiMacExtCct
wfFddiMacExtCct.description: Circuit number associated with a MAC entity.

wfFddiMacFrameStatusFunctions.name: wfFddiMacFrameStatusFunctions
wfFddiMacFrameStatusFunctions.description: Indicates the MAC's optional Frame Status processing functions. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value 0, then for each function present, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: function power -------- ----- fs-repeating 0 fs-setting 1 fs-clearing 2

wfFddiMacBridgeFunctions.name: wfFddiMacBridgeFunctions
wfFddiMacBridgeFunctions.description: Indicates the MAC's optional bridging functions. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each function present, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Function Power -------- ---- tb 0 -- Transparent bridging active sr 1 -- Src routing active srt 2 -- Src routing transparent active

wfFddiMacTMaxCapability.name: wfFddiMacTMaxCapability
wfFddiMacTMaxCapability.description: Indicates the maximum time value (in nanoseconds) of 'wfFddiMacTMax' that this MAC can support.

wfFddiMacTvxCapability.name: wfFddiMacTvxCapability
wfFddiMacTvxCapability.description: Indicates the maximum time value (in nanoseconds) of 'wfFddiMacTvxValue' that this MAC can support.

wfFddiMacAvailablePaths.name: wfFddiMacAvailablePaths
wfFddiMacAvailablePaths.description: Indicates the paths available for this MAC. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value 0, then for each type of PATH that this MAC has available, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Path Power ---- ----- Primary 0 Secondary 1 Local 2

wfFddiMacCurrentPath.name: wfFddiMacCurrentPath
wfFddiMacCurrentPath.description: Indicates the Path into which this MAC is currently inserted.

wfFddiMacRequestedPaths.name: wfFddiMacRequestedPaths
wfFddiMacRequestedPaths.description: Contains a list of Permitted Paths which specifies the Path(s) into which the MAC may be inserted. The value is a sum which represents the individual paths that are desired. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each type of PATH that this node is, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Path Power ---- ----- local 0 secondary-alternate 1 primary-alternate 2 concatenated-alternate 3 secondary-preferred 4 primary-preferred 5 concatenated-preferred 6 thru 7

wfFddiMacCopiedCts.name: wfFddiMacCopiedCts
wfFddiMacCopiedCts.description: A count that should as closely as possible match the number of frames addressed to (A bit set) and successfully copied into the station's receive buffers (C bit set) by this MAC.

wfFddiMacFrameErrorThreshold.name: wfFddiMacFrameErrorThreshold
wfFddiMacFrameErrorThreshold.description: Specifies the Mac Frame Error Threshold for determining when a MAC Frame Error Condition report will be generated (via an SRF Frame). If Mac Frame Error Ratio is greater than Mac Frame Error Threshold then the Mac Frame Error Condition exists. This Mac Frame Error Ratio is calculated periodically based on the attributes wfFddiMacErrorCts and wfFddiMacLostCts. A low value of Mac Frame Error Threshold will generate more frequent Mac Frame Error conditions if the wfFddiMacErrorCts and wfFddiMacLostCts counters are periodically increased. Therefore the user should set the Mac Frame Error Threshold (1..65535) in accordance with the volatility of the ring.

wfFddiMacFrameErrorRatio.name: wfFddiMacFrameErrorRatio
wfFddiMacFrameErrorRatio.description: This variable is the value of the ratio: ((delta wfFddiMacLostCts + delta wfFddiMacErrorCts) / (delta wfFddiMacFrameCts + delta wfFddiMacLostCts)) 2**16)

wfFddiMacHardwarePresent.name: wfFddiMacHardwarePresent
wfFddiMacHardwarePresent.description: This variable indicates the presence of underlying hardware support for this MAC object.

wfFddiMacMaUnitDataEnable.name: wfFddiMacMaUnitDataEnable
wfFddiMacMaUnitDataEnable.description: A configurable attribute that specifies whether the MAC will be available for the transmission and reception of Protocol Data Units (PDUs). If enabled, the interface to the MAC entity will be available for the exchange of PDUs between the MAC and the local LLC entity when the ring becomes operational (i.e., LLC interface is established). Setting this attribute has no effect on the transfer and reception of MAC or SMT frames.

wfFddiMacTvxExpiredCts.name: wfFddiMacTvxExpiredCts
wfFddiMacTvxExpiredCts.description: A count that should as closely as possible match the number of times that TVX has expired.

wfFddiMacLateCts.name: wfFddiMacLateCts
wfFddiMacLateCts.description: A count that should as closely as possible match the number of TRT expirations since this MAC was reset or a token was received.

wfFddiMacRingOpCts.name: wfFddiMacRingOpCts
wfFddiMacRingOpCts.description: The count of the number of times the ring has entered the 'Ring Operational' state from the `Ring Not Operational' state. This count is updated when a SM_MA_STATUS Indication of a change in the Ring_Operational state occurs. Because of implementatio considerations, this count may be less than the actual RingOp_Ct. It is not a requirement that this count be exact.

wfFddiMacDuplicateTokenCts.name: wfFddiMacDuplicateTokenCts
wfFddiMacDuplicateTokenCts.description: The count of the number of times a Duplicate Token has been detected.

wfFddiPathEntry.name: wfFddiPathEntry
wfFddiPathEntry.description: A PATH entry containing information common to a given PATH.

wfFddiPathSlot.name: wfFddiPathSlot
wfFddiPathSlot.description: Slot number associated with a PATH entity.

wfFddiPathNode.name: wfFddiPathNode
wfFddiPathNode.description: Node/connector number associated with a PATH entity.

wfFddiPathCct.name: wfFddiPathCct
wfFddiPathCct.description: Circuit number associated with a PATH entity.

wfFddiPathConfiguration.name: wfFddiPathConfiguration
wfFddiPathConfiguration.description: A circular list of resources on the path where each entry in the list consists of a resource type identifier (MAC or PORT), an index, and its CurrentPath. If the path is available to a resource in the node (as indicated by 'wfFddiPortAvailablePaths' or 'wfFddiMacAvailablePaths') then that resource shall be included in the list. If the path is not available to a resource or the underlying hardware is not present, then that resource shall not be included in the list. Resources currently inserted in the Path shall appear in the list once in token order. Resources not currently inserted in the Path shall appear once in any position supported by the implementation.

wfFddiPathExtTable.name: wfFddiPathExtTable
wfFddiPathExtTable.description: A list of PATH extension entries.

wfFddiPathExtEntry.name: wfFddiPathExtEntry
wfFddiPathExtEntry.description: A PATH entry containing information common to a given PATH.

wfFddiPathExtSlot.name: wfFddiPathExtSlot
wfFddiPathExtSlot.description: Slot number associated with a Path entity.

wfFddiPathExtNode.name: wfFddiPathExtNode
wfFddiPathExtNode.description: Node/connector number associated with a Path entity.

wfFddiPathExtCct.name: wfFddiPathExtCct
wfFddiPathExtCct.description: Circuit number associated with a Path entity.

wfFddiPathTvxLowerBound.name: wfFddiPathTvxLowerBound
wfFddiPathTvxLowerBound.description: Specifies the minimum time value of 'wfFddiMacTvxValue' that shall be used by any MAC that is configured in this path. The operational value of 'wfFddiMacTvxValue' is managed by setting this variable. This variable has the time value range of: 0 < wfFddiPathTvxLowerBound < wfFddiPathMaxTReq Changes to this attribute shall either satisfy the time value relationship: wfFddiPathTvxLowerBound <= wfFddiMacTvxCapability of each of the MACS currently on the path, or be considered out of range. Time specified in nanoseconds. The initial value of wfFddiPathTvxLowerBound shall be 2.500 msec.

wfFddiPathTMaxLowerBound.name: wfFddiPathTMaxLowerBound
wfFddiPathTMaxLowerBound.description: Specifies the minimum time value of 'wfFddiMACTMax' that shall be used by any MAC that is configured in this path. The operational value of 'wfFddiMacTMax' is managed by setting this attribute. This attribute has the time value range of: wfFddiPathMaxTReq <= wfFddiPathTMaxLowerBound and an absolute time value range of 10msec <= wfFddiPathTMaxLowerBound. Changes to this aattribute shall either satisfy the time value relationship: wfFddiPathTMaxLowerBound < wfFddiMacTMaxCapability of each of the MACs currently on the path, or be considered out of range. Time specified in nanoseconds. The initial value of wfFddiPathTMaxLowerBound shall be 165 msec.

wfFddiPathMaxTReq.name: wfFddiPathMaxTReq
wfFddiPathMaxTReq.description: This variable is the T_Req_value passed to the MAC. Without having detected a duplicate, the time value of this variable shall assume the maximum supported time value which is less than or equal to the time value of wfFDDIMacTReq. When a MAC has an address detected as a duplicate, it may use a time value for this variable greater than the time value of wfFddiPathTMaxLowerBound. A station shall cause claim when the new T_Req may cause the value of T_Neg to change in the claim process (i.e., time value new T_Req < T_Neg, or old T_Req = T_Neg). This value is encoded in nanoseconds. The name of this attribute in the IETF MIB is FddiMibMACTReq.

wfFddiPortEntry.name: wfFddiPortEntry
wfFddiPortEntry.description: A PORT entry containing information common to a given PORT.

wfFddiPortSlot.name: wfFddiPortSlot
wfFddiPortSlot.description: Slot number associated with a PORT entity.

wfFddiPortNode.name: wfFddiPortNode
wfFddiPortNode.description: Node/connector number associated with a PORT entity.

wfFddiPortCct.name: wfFddiPortCct
wfFddiPortCct.description: Circuit number associated with a PORT entity.

wfFddiPortIndex.name: wfFddiPortIndex
wfFddiPortIndex.description: A unique value for each PORT associated with each slot/connector pair.

wfFddiPortPcType.name: wfFddiPortPcType
wfFddiPortPcType.description: The physical connector type of the local PORT.

wfFddiPortPcNeighbor.name: wfFddiPortPcNeighbor
wfFddiPortPcNeighbor.description: The physical connector type of the remote PORT.

wfFddiPortRequestedPaths.name: wfFddiPortRequestedPaths
wfFddiPortRequestedPaths.description: This variable is a list of permitted paths where each list element defines the Port's permitted paths. The first octet corresponds to 'none', the second octet to 'tree' and the third octet to 'peer'.

wfFddiPortBsFlag.name: wfFddiPortBsFlag
wfFddiPortBsFlag.description: Break State Flag - A PCM flag used to indicate that the PCM state Machine is not leaving the Break State in an expected time interval & a problem is suspected.

wfFddiPortLerFlag.name: wfFddiPortLerFlag
wfFddiPortLerFlag.description: The condition becomes active when the value of 'wfFddiPortLerEstimate' is <= 'wfFddiPortLerAlarm'. This will be reported with Status Report Frames (SRF).

wfFddiPortConnectState.name: wfFddiPortConnectState
wfFddiPortConnectState.description: A variable from PCM to other management entities indicating the state of the connection.

wfFddiPortMacIndicated.name: wfFddiPortMacIndicated
wfFddiPortMacIndicated.description: The indications (T_Val(9), R_Val(9)) in PC-Signalling, of the intent to place a MAC in the output token path to a PORT.

wfFddiPortExtTable.name: wfFddiPortExtTable
wfFddiPortExtTable.description: A list of PORT extension entries.

wfFddiPortExtEntry.name: wfFddiPortExtEntry
wfFddiPortExtEntry.description: A PORT entry containing information common to a given PORT.

wfFddiPortExtSlot.name: wfFddiPortExtSlot
wfFddiPortExtSlot.description: Slot number associated with a Port entity.

wfFddiPortExtNode.name: wfFddiPortExtNode
wfFddiPortExtNode.description: Node/connector number associated with a Port entity.

wfFddiPortExtCct.name: wfFddiPortExtCct
wfFddiPortExtCct.description: Circuit number associated with a Port entity.

wfFddiPortExtIndex.name: wfFddiPortExtIndex
wfFddiPortExtIndex.description: A unique value for each PORT associated with each slot/connector pair.

wfFddiPortConnectionPolicies.name: wfFddiPortConnectionPolicies
wfFddiPortConnectionPolicies.description: A value representing the PORT's connection policies desired in the node. The value of 'pc-mac-lct' (i.e. PCM MAC LinkConfidence Test) is a term used in the PC_MAC_LCT Flag. The value of 'pc-mac-loop' is a term used in the PC_MAC_LOOP flag. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each PORT policy, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Policy Power ------ ----- pc-mac-lct 0 pc-mac-loop 1

wfFddiPortCurrentPath.name: wfFddiPortCurrentPath
wfFddiPortCurrentPath.description: Indicates the Path(s) into which this PORT is currently inserted.

wfFddiPortMacPlacement.name: wfFddiPortMacPlacement
wfFddiPortMacPlacement.description: Indicates the MAC, if any, whose transmit path exits the station via this PORT. The value shall be zero if there is no MAC associated with the PORT.

wfFddiPortAvailablePaths.name: wfFddiPortAvailablePaths
wfFddiPortAvailablePaths.description: Indicates the Paths which are available to this Port. In the absence of faults, the A & B ports will always have both the Primary & Secondary paths available. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value 0, then for each type of PATH that this port has available, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Path Power ---- ----- Primary 0 Secondary 1 Local 2

wfFddiPortPmdClass.name: wfFddiPortPmdClass
wfFddiPortPmdClass.description: Indicates the Path(s) into which this PORT is currently inserted.

wfFddiPortConnectionCapabilities.name: wfFddiPortConnectionCapabilities
wfFddiPortConnectionCapabilities.description: A value that indicates the connection capabilities of the port. The 'pc-mac-lct' bit indicates that the station has the capability of setting the PC_MAC_LCT Flag. The 'pc-mac-loop' bit indicates that the station has the capability of setting the PC_MAC_LOOP Flag. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each PORT policy, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Capability Power ---------- ----- pc-mac-lct 0 pc-mac-loop 1

wfFddiPortEbErrorCts.name: wfFddiPortEbErrorCts
wfFddiPortEbErrorCts.description: The count of the number of elasticity buffer errors for a particular PHY. The elasticity buffer is used to account for clock tolerances between stations

wfFddiPortLctFailCts.name: wfFddiPortLctFailCts
wfFddiPortLctFailCts.description: The count of the consecutive times the link confidence test (LCT) has failed during Connection Management.

wfFddiPortLerEstimate.name: wfFddiPortLerEstimate
wfFddiPortLerEstimate.description: A long term average of the link error rate. It ranges from 10**-4 to 10**-15 and is reported as the absolute value of the base 10 logarithm.

wfFddiPortLemRejectCts.name: wfFddiPortLemRejectCts
wfFddiPortLemRejectCts.description: A link error monitoring count of the times that a link has been rejected.

wfFddiPortLemCts.name: wfFddiPortLemCts
wfFddiPortLemCts.description: The aggregate link error moniitor error count, set to 0 only on station initialization.

wfFddiPortLerCutOff.name: wfFddiPortLerCutOff
wfFddiPortLerCutOff.description: The link err rate estimate at which a link connection will be broken. It ranges from 10**-4 to 10**-15 and is reported as the absolute value of the base 10 logarithm.

wfFddiPortLerAlarm.name: wfFddiPortLerAlarm
wfFddiPortLerAlarm.description: The link err rate estimate at which a link connection will generate an alarm. It ranges from 10**-4 to 10**-15 and is reported as the absolute value of the base 10 logarithm of the estimate.

wfFddiPortPcWithhold.name: wfFddiPortPcWithhold
wfFddiPortPcWithhold.description: A variable from PCM to other management entities containing the reason for withholding a connection.

wfFddiPortHardwarePresent.name: wfFddiPortHardwarePresent
wfFddiPortHardwarePresent.description: This variable indicates the presence of underlying hardware support for this port object.

wfFddiPortActionTable.name: wfFddiPortActionTable
wfFddiPortActionTable.description: A list of Port Action entries.

wfFddiPortActionEntry.name: wfFddiPortActionEntry
wfFddiPortActionEntry.description: A PORT entry containing actions common to a given PORT.

wfFddiPortActionSlot.name: wfFddiPortActionSlot
wfFddiPortActionSlot.description: Slot number associated with a PORT action entity.

wfFddiPortActionNode.name: wfFddiPortActionNode
wfFddiPortActionNode.description: Node/connector number associated with a PORT action entity.

wfFddiPortActionCct.name: wfFddiPortActionCct
wfFddiPortActionCct.description: Circuit number associated with a PORT action entity.

wfFddiPortActionIndex.name: wfFddiPortActionIndex
wfFddiPortActionIndex.description: A unique value for each PORT associated with each slot/connector pair.

wfFddiPortAction.name: wfFddiPortAction
wfFddiPortAction.description: Causes a control signal to be generated with a control_action of 'Signal' and the 'variable' parameter set with the appropriate value (i.e. PC_Maint, PC_Enable, PC_Disable, PC_Start, or PC_Stop). These signals are used to initiate a state change within Connection Management

wfFddiXLineCfgEntry.name: wfFddiXLineCfgEntry
wfFddiXLineCfgEntry.description: An FDDI entry containing configuration parameters about an FDDI interface.

wfFddiXLineCfgDelete.name: wfFddiXLineCfgDelete
wfFddiXLineCfgDelete.description: FDDI interface table create/delete object. The default setting is create.

wfFddiXLineCfgEnable.name: wfFddiXLineCfgEnable
wfFddiXLineCfgEnable.description: FDDI interface enable/disable object. The default setting is enable.

wfFddiXLineCfgLossOfServiceTmo.name: wfFddiXLineCfgLossOfServiceTmo
wfFddiXLineCfgLossOfServiceTmo.description: This timer (in seconds) provides debounce functionality for an FDDI interface. When the FDDI ring becomes non-operational, the LLC interface will be disabled if the following conditions hold TRUE: 1. fddimibMACMAUnitdataEnable (contained in fddimibMACTable of rfc1512.mib) is enabled 2. This FDDI interface has been unavailable for wfFddiXLineCfgLossOfServiceTmo seconds. If the FDDI interface becomes enabled before wfFddiXLineCfgLossOfServiceTmo expires, then the timer is cancelled and nothing occurs. This debounce timer may be disabled by setting it to 0. In this case, when the FDDI interface becomes non-operational, the LLC interface will be notified right away.

wfFddiXLineCfgSmtEnable.name: wfFddiXLineCfgSmtEnable
wfFddiXLineCfgSmtEnable.description: Enable Station Management periodic timers and NIF protocol.

wfFddiXLineCfgSmtDatProtocol.name: wfFddiXLineCfgSmtDatProtocol
wfFddiXLineCfgSmtDatProtocol.description: SMT will implement an optional ANSI duplicate address test involving periodic transmission of NSA NIF frames addressed to itself if enabled by this attribute.

wfFddiXLineCfgLineNumber.name: wfFddiXLineCfgLineNumber
wfFddiXLineCfgLineNumber.description: Logical line number associated with this driver entity.

wfFddiXLineCfgForcePeerTree.name: wfFddiXLineCfgForcePeerTree
wfFddiXLineCfgForcePeerTree.description: This attribute allows all FDDI Peer/Tree connections to reach the 'Thru' state. This is done to give the user some flexibility and allow them to Daisy Chain their Phy connections, mixing Tree & Peer connections. This type of daisy chaining DOES NOT conform to the SMT standard and is NOT recommended as it may result in a less than optimum token path. Normally when we have a Peer/Tree connection mix, we will wrap the connection, favoring PHY B.

wfFddiXLineCfgSlot.name: wfFddiXLineCfgSlot
wfFddiXLineCfgSlot.description: Chassis slot number of FDDI interface.

wfFddiXLineCfgModule.name: wfFddiXLineCfgModule
wfFddiXLineCfgModule.description: Module number for Fiddlestix platform, filled in by driver.

wfFddiXLineCfgActualNode.name: wfFddiXLineCfgActualNode
wfFddiXLineCfgActualNode.description: Actual Node number for this FDDI interface, filled in by the driver.

wfFddiXLineCfgNode.name: wfFddiXLineCfgNode
wfFddiXLineCfgNode.description: Instance ID node - filled in by driver. This attribute is an encoded value and is equal to 'module'*100 + 'node'. Where 'module' is defined in object 4 and 'node' is defined in object 5 of this table.

wfFddiXLineCfgSmtIndex.name: wfFddiXLineCfgSmtIndex
wfFddiXLineCfgSmtIndex.description: Used for indexing into rfc1512 MIBS, this value is gotten from multiplying the 'slot*1000' and then adding the 'wfFddiXLineCfgNode' attribute described above. Its purpose is to uniquely identify each SMT which exists.

wfFddiXLineCfgIfIndex.name: wfFddiXLineCfgIfIndex
wfFddiXLineCfgIfIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an interface to a FDDI-like medium. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wfFddiXLineEntry.name: wfFddiXLineEntry
wfFddiXLineEntry.description: An FDDI entry containing information about an FDDI interface.

wfFddiXLineSlot.name: wfFddiXLineSlot
wfFddiXLineSlot.description: Chassis slot number of FDDI interface.

wfFddiXLineModule.name: wfFddiXLineModule
wfFddiXLineModule.description: Module number for Fiddlestix platform, filled in by driver.

wfFddiXLineActualNode.name: wfFddiXLineActualNode
wfFddiXLineActualNode.description: Actual Node number for this FDDI interface, filled in by the driver.

wfFddiXLineNode.name: wfFddiXLineNode
wfFddiXLineNode.description: Instance ID node - filled in by driver. This attribute is an encoded value and is equal to 'module'*10 + 'node'. Where 'module' is defined in object 4 and 'node' is defined in object 5 of this table.

wfFddiXLineSmtIndex.name: wfFddiXLineSmtIndex
wfFddiXLineSmtIndex.description: Logical line number associated with this FDDI interface.

wfFddiXLineIfIndex.name: wfFddiXLineIfIndex
wfFddiXLineIfIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an interface to a FDDI-like medium. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wfFddiXLineTxErrors.name: wfFddiXLineTxErrors
wfFddiXLineTxErrors.description: An aggregate of the total number of transmit errors on this FDDI interface.

wfFddiXLineTxAborts.name: wfFddiXLineTxAborts
wfFddiXLineTxAborts.description: Number of transmitted frames terminated (i.e. aborted) abnormally by the MAC.

wfFddiXLineTxOverruns.name: wfFddiXLineTxOverruns
wfFddiXLineTxOverruns.description: Number of tranmitter overruns experienced by this interface. May indicate a HW problem with regards to the DMAC feeding the MAC.

wfFddiXLineTxUnderruns.name: wfFddiXLineTxUnderruns
wfFddiXLineTxUnderruns.description: Number of tranmitter underruns experienced by this interface. May indicate a SW problem with regards to replenishing the DMACs XMT descriptor.

wfFddiXLineRxErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxErrors
wfFddiXLineRxErrors.description: An aggregate of the total number of receive errors on this FDDI interface.

wfFddiXLineRxCrcErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxCrcErrors
wfFddiXLineRxCrcErrors.description: Number of LLC frames received with CRC errors.

wfFddiXLineRxSmtCrcErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxSmtCrcErrors
wfFddiXLineRxSmtCrcErrors.description: Number of SMT frames received with CRC errors.

wfFddiXLineRxInvalidFrameStatusErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxInvalidFrameStatusErrors
wfFddiXLineRxInvalidFrameStatusErrors.description: A count of the number of badly formed LLC frames received off of the FDDI ring. These are frames which do not contain a valid Frame Status field of at least 3 control indicator symbols (i.e. E, A, C, flags).

wfFddiXLineRxSmtInvalidFrameStatusErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxSmtInvalidFrameStatusErrors
wfFddiXLineRxSmtInvalidFrameStatusErrors.description: A count of the number of badly formed SMT frames received off of the FDDI ring. These are frames which do not contain a valid Frame Status field of at least 3 control indicator symbols (i.e. E, A, C, flags).

wfFddiXLineRxMacErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxMacErrors
wfFddiXLineRxMacErrors.description: Number of LLC frames received with MAC errors.

wfFddiXLineRxSmtMacErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxSmtMacErrors
wfFddiXLineRxSmtMacErrors.description: Number of SMT frames received with MAC errors.

wfFddiXLineRxFormatErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxFormatErrors
wfFddiXLineRxFormatErrors.description: Number of LLC frames received with Format errors.

wfFddiXLineRxSmtFormatErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxSmtFormatErrors
wfFddiXLineRxSmtFormatErrors.description: Number of SMT frames received with Format errors.

wfFddiXLineRxFragmentErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxFragmentErrors
wfFddiXLineRxFragmentErrors.description: Number of LLC frame fragments received.

wfFddiXLineRxSmtFragmentErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxSmtFragmentErrors
wfFddiXLineRxSmtFragmentErrors.description: Number of SMT frame fragments received.

wfFddiXLineRxInvalidLengthErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxInvalidLengthErrors
wfFddiXLineRxInvalidLengthErrors.description: Number of LLC frames received with an ending T symbol which are either too short or contain an odd number of symbols.

wfFddiXLineRxSmtInvalidLengthErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxSmtInvalidLengthErrors
wfFddiXLineRxSmtInvalidLengthErrors.description: Number of SMT frames received with an ending T symbol which are either too short or contain an odd number of symbols.

wfFddiXLineRxAbortErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxAbortErrors
wfFddiXLineRxAbortErrors.description: Number of LLC frames aborted during reception.

wfFddiXLineRxSmtAbortErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxSmtAbortErrors
wfFddiXLineRxSmtAbortErrors.description: Number of LLC frames aborted during reception.

wfFddiXLineRxEDataUnknownErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxEDataUnknownErrors
wfFddiXLineRxEDataUnknownErrors.description: Number of LLC frames received with the Error indication set, that we couldn't decode as were unable to get the END_DATA value from the frame.

wfFddiXLineRxSmtEDataUnknownErrors.name: wfFddiXLineRxSmtEDataUnknownErrors
wfFddiXLineRxSmtEDataUnknownErrors.description: Number of SMT frames received with the Error indication set, that we couldn't decode as were unable to get the END_DATA value from the frame.

wfFddiXLineRxLastEDataFStatusErrorVal.name: wfFddiXLineRxLastEDataFStatusErrorVal
wfFddiXLineRxLastEDataFStatusErrorVal.description: The value of END_DATA and FRAME_STATUS from the last LLC frame received containing an error.

wfFddiXLineRxSmtLastEDataFStatusErrorVal.name: wfFddiXLineRxSmtLastEDataFStatusErrorVal
wfFddiXLineRxSmtLastEDataFStatusErrorVal.description: The value of END_DATA and FRAME_STATUS from the last SMT frame received containing an error.

wfFddiXLineRxOverruns.name: wfFddiXLineRxOverruns
wfFddiXLineRxOverruns.description: Number of receiver overruns experienced by this interface. May indicate a SW problem with regards to replenishing the DMACs RCV descriptors.

wfFddiXLineRxUnderruns.name: wfFddiXLineRxUnderruns
wfFddiXLineRxUnderruns.description: Number of receiver underruns experienced by this interface. May indicate a HW problem with regards to the DMAC feeding the MAC.

wfFddiXLineRxOversizedFrames.name: wfFddiXLineRxOversizedFrames
wfFddiXLineRxOversizedFrames.description: Number of LLC frames received whose length exceeded the MTU. (Note: The MTU is defined in rfc1573 in the ifMtu object.)

wfFddiXLineRxSmtOversizedFrames.name: wfFddiXLineRxSmtOversizedFrames
wfFddiXLineRxSmtOversizedFrames.description: Number of SMT frames received whose length exceeded the MTU. (Note: The MTU is defined in rfc1573 in the ifMtu object.)

wfFddiXLineRxUndersizedFrames.name: wfFddiXLineRxUndersizedFrames
wfFddiXLineRxUndersizedFrames.description: Number of LLC frames received whose length was less than 20 bytes, including the FC byte and a 4 byte CRC.

wfFddiXLineRxSmtUndersizedFrames.name: wfFddiXLineRxSmtUndersizedFrames
wfFddiXLineRxSmtUndersizedFrames.description: Number of SMT frames received whose length was less than 37 bytes, including the FC byte and a 4 byte CRC.

wfFddiXLineRxSmtSecondaryNsaFrames.name: wfFddiXLineRxSmtSecondaryNsaFrames
wfFddiXLineRxSmtSecondaryNsaFrames.description: Number of Secondary NSA frames received by this interface and dropped.

wfFddiXLineUnexpectedFrames.name: wfFddiXLineUnexpectedFrames
wfFddiXLineUnexpectedFrames.description: Number of non-LLC and non SMT frames received by this interface. Does NOT include MAC frames or Void frames.

wfFddiXLineRxSmtOctets.name: wfFddiXLineRxSmtOctets
wfFddiXLineRxSmtOctets.description: Number of bytes received without error. This byte count only includes SMT frames (i.e. no MAC and LLC frames).

wfFddiXLineRxSmtFrames.name: wfFddiXLineRxSmtFrames
wfFddiXLineRxSmtFrames.description: Number of frames received without error. This frame count only includes SMT frames (i.e. no MAC and LLC frames).

wfFddiXLineTxSmtOctets.name: wfFddiXLineTxSmtOctets
wfFddiXLineTxSmtOctets.description: Number of bytes transmitted. This byte count only includes SMT frames (i.e. no MAC and LLC frames). Also note that this value is an approximation in that its assumed frames queued for transmit ALWAYS make it onto the ring.

wfFddiXLineTxSmtFrames.name: wfFddiXLineTxSmtFrames
wfFddiXLineTxSmtFrames.description: Number of frames transmitted. This frame count only includes SMT frames (i.e. no MAC and LLC frames). Also note that this value is an approximation in that its assumed frames queued for transmit ALWAYS make it onto the ring.

wfFddiXLinePhyALogPtr.name: wfFddiXLinePhyALogPtr
wfFddiXLinePhyALogPtr.description: Address of the Debug Phy Event Buffer for Phy A. This attribute is strictly for diagnostic purposes. The size of the buffer is 1028 bytes.

wfFddiXLinePhyBLogPtr.name: wfFddiXLinePhyBLogPtr
wfFddiXLinePhyBLogPtr.description: Address of the Debug Phy Event Buffer for Phy B. This attribute is strictly for diagnostic purposes. The size of the buffer is 1028 bytes.

wfFddiXSmtEntry.name: wfFddiXSmtEntry
wfFddiXSmtEntry.description: An FDDI entry containing information about an FDDI interface.

wfFddiXSmtIndex.name: wfFddiXSmtIndex
wfFddiXSmtIndex.description: A unique value for each SMT. The value for each SMT must remain constant at least from one re- initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

wfFddiXSmtManufacturerData.name: wfFddiXSmtManufacturerData
wfFddiXSmtManufacturerData.description: Contains 32 Octets of manufacturer data. The first component, manufacturing OUI, is the 3 octet Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI) assigned by IEEE. The second component, ManufacturerData, is the manufacturers data (29 octets).

wfFddiXMacEntry.name: wfFddiXMacEntry
wfFddiXMacEntry.description: An FDDI entry containing information about an FDDI interface.

wfFddiXMacSmtIndex.name: wfFddiXMacSmtIndex
wfFddiXMacSmtIndex.description: The value of the SMT index associated with this MAC.

wfFddiXMacIndex.name: wfFddiXMacIndex
wfFddiXMacIndex.description: Index variable for uniquely identifying the MAC object instances, which is the same as the corresponding resource index in SMT.

wfFddiXMacBridgeFunctions.name: wfFddiXMacBridgeFunctions
wfFddiXMacBridgeFunctions.description: Indicates the MAC's optional bridging functions. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each function present, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Function Power -------- ---- tb 0 -- Transparent bridging active sr 1 -- Src routing active srt 2 -- Src routing transparent active

wfFddiXMacDuplicateTokenCts.name: wfFddiXMacDuplicateTokenCts
wfFddiXMacDuplicateTokenCts.description: The count of the number of times a Duplicate Token has been detected.

wfFddiXPortEntry.name: wfFddiXPortEntry
wfFddiXPortEntry.description: An FDDI entry containing information about an FDDI interface.

wfFddiXPortSmtIndex.name: wfFddiXPortSmtIndex
wfFddiXPortSmtIndex.description: The value of the SMT index associated with this PORT.

wfFddiXPortIndex.name: wfFddiXPortIndex
wfFddiXPortIndex.description: A unique value for each PORT within a given SMT, which is the same as the corresponding resource index in SMT. The value for each PORT must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

wfFddiXPortEbErrors.name: wfFddiXPortEbErrors
wfFddiXPortEbErrors.description: The count of the number of elasticity buffer errors for a particular PHY. The elasticity buffer is used to account for clock tolerances between stations.
